WEBVTT

00:08.802 --> 00:10.202
It's supposed to be
a good school.

00:10.204 --> 00:12.037
Yeah, parents pumped
a lot of money into it.

00:12.039 --> 00:12.972
You know the place?

00:12.974 --> 00:14.206
Caught a case here
a while back.

00:14.208 --> 00:15.174
What do we got?

00:15.176 --> 00:16.976
Ten-year-old female,
Jenna Wallace.

00:16.978 --> 00:18.244
Never made it home
from school.

00:18.246 --> 00:20.379
Parents over there reported
her missing an hour ago.

00:20.381 --> 00:21.480
Any witnesses?

00:21.482 --> 00:23.349
Crossing guard saw
the girl leave the building.

00:23.351 --> 00:25.484
Ma'am, can you tell us
what you saw?

00:25.486 --> 00:27.386
Uh, Jenna had just
crossed the street,

00:27.388 --> 00:30.456
um, a white car pulled up,
a two-door compact sedan,

00:30.458 --> 00:32.124
um, she got in,
they took off.

00:32.125 --> 00:33.726
Did you get a look
at the driver?

00:33.728 --> 00:36.262
No. I didn't catch
the license plate either.

00:36.264 --> 00:38.197
Does Jenna usually get
picked up from school?

00:38.199 --> 00:40.499
No, tha-tha-that's the thing...

00:40.501 --> 00:42.968
she walks home every day
with her friend Stacy.

00:42.970 --> 00:43.936
Really nice kids.

00:43.938 --> 00:45.337
No signs of struggle, huh?

00:45.339 --> 00:47.706
No. The way she got
in the car,

00:47.708 --> 00:50.709
it seemed like
she knew the driver.

00:50.711 --> 00:52.378
I keep thinking
I should've done something.

00:52.380 --> 00:54.680
You've been very helpful,
thank you.

00:54.682 --> 00:56.015
I got a bad feeling
about this one.

00:56.017 --> 00:57.580
At least we got the
make and model of the car.

00:57.605 --> 00:58.518
Yeah.

00:58.519 --> 00:59.685
Excuse us.
Detective Reagan.

00:59.687 --> 01:01.220
This is Detective Baez.

01:01.222 --> 01:02.421
You need to find Jenna.

01:02.423 --> 01:04.390
You need to bring
her back to us.

01:04.391 --> 01:05.391
We're gonna do
everything we can.

01:05.393 --> 01:06.892
We'd like for you
two to come down

01:06.894 --> 01:09.094
to the squad room so we can
ask you some questions.

01:09.096 --> 01:10.429
The more information we get,

01:10.431 --> 01:12.431
the better chances are we
can get your daughter back.

01:12.433 --> 01:14.366
Please, you need
to find my baby.

01:14.368 --> 01:15.968
We'll do all we
can, all right?

01:15.970 --> 01:17.425
Get them down to
squad, all right?

01:17.426 --> 01:18.491
Yes, sir.

01:18.639 --> 01:20.005
Start plastering this
neighborhood with

01:20.007 --> 01:21.607
"information wanted" posters.

01:21.609 --> 01:23.576
I'll let Gormley know we need
the whole squad on this.

01:23.578 --> 01:25.444
We got about 72 hours
to find this girl

01:25.446 --> 01:27.813
or chances are we never will.

01:30.650 --> 01:33.152
Ms. Del Rio ran down
the superintendent

01:33.154 --> 01:34.987
in the parking garage
of her building.

01:34.989 --> 01:37.756
I understand the allegations
against Ms. Del Rio.

01:37.758 --> 01:39.124
We have an eyewitness.

01:39.126 --> 01:42.695
Elderly lady and the lighting
was not great, I know that.

01:42.697 --> 01:44.830
I'm so sorry I hurt
Mr. Romanelli. I--

01:44.832 --> 01:46.031
I'm sorry.

01:46.033 --> 01:48.334
You put Mr. Romanelli
in the morgue, ma'am.

01:48.336 --> 01:51.670
That said, in the absence
of concrete proof

01:51.672 --> 01:53.205
that you intended
to kill the victim,

01:53.207 --> 01:55.641
I am prepared to offer
a plea of manslaughter.

01:55.643 --> 01:57.009
That's generous...

01:57.011 --> 01:59.044
in the normal
course of events.

01:59.046 --> 02:01.747
But not in this case,
no, thank you.

02:01.749 --> 02:03.916
I think you should confer
with your client first.

02:03.918 --> 02:05.584
The evidence is overwhelming.

02:05.586 --> 02:11.357
Ms. Del Rio suffers from, uh,
severe bipolar illness.

02:11.359 --> 02:13.759
And she was in a manic state
at the time of the accident...

02:13.761 --> 02:15.294
You're pleading not guilty
by reason of

02:15.296 --> 02:16.962
mental disease or defect.

02:16.964 --> 02:19.498
That is very difficult to prove.

02:19.500 --> 02:22.167
Exactly... but that's why
they pay me the big bucks.

02:29.676 --> 02:32.011
I understand.

02:32.013 --> 02:34.413
Thanks for the call.

02:34.415 --> 02:36.081
That was Scotland Yard.

02:36.083 --> 02:38.117
Please don't tell me
we're going on another

02:38.119 --> 02:39.518
goodwill trip to London.

02:39.520 --> 02:41.287
That rain's murder
on my sciatica.

02:41.289 --> 02:43.923
There is not a lot of goodwill
flowing at the moment.

02:43.925 --> 02:46.592
They've detained one
of our intelligence officers,

02:46.594 --> 02:48.160
Detective Paul Hailey.

02:48.162 --> 02:49.495
On what charge?

02:49.497 --> 02:51.497
There was a terrorist bombing
at a West End tube station.

02:51.499 --> 02:52.865
I know that.

02:52.867 --> 02:54.300
Hailey is being accused

02:54.302 --> 02:56.602
of entering the scene
and handling evidence

02:56.604 --> 02:58.971
without authorization.
He's doing his job.

02:58.973 --> 03:02.107
Yeah! He found the cause of the
blast and reported his findings.

03:02.109 --> 03:03.075
What'd he find?

03:04.946 --> 03:07.146
That's all I can tell you.

03:07.148 --> 03:10.115
That's all you <i>can</i> tell me
or all you <i>will</i> tell me?

03:12.053 --> 03:14.386
I can't handle this if
I don't know what's going on!

03:14.388 --> 03:15.387
There's nothing to handle.

03:15.389 --> 03:16.355
You know there will be.

03:16.357 --> 03:19.325
Garrett, you are
my deputy commissioner

03:19.327 --> 03:20.793
of public information.

03:20.795 --> 03:22.561
This is private information.

03:26.232 --> 03:28.300
So, what do we
got on your end?

03:28.302 --> 03:29.668
We're canvassing
the neighborhood,

03:29.670 --> 03:32.037
checking all the surveillance
cameras near the school,

03:32.039 --> 03:34.473
running all vehicles
matching the description

03:34.475 --> 03:36.342
registered in the area.
Good.

03:36.344 --> 03:37.710
I'll get TARU to download
their content

03:37.712 --> 03:39.411
from the past few days...
Sounds like a plan.

03:39.413 --> 03:41.246
I'm running all recent parolees.
Here you go, Reagan.

03:41.248 --> 03:42.247
Thank you.

03:42.249 --> 03:44.583
Checking the sex
offender registry...

03:44.585 --> 03:47.219
see if there's any twists
living in the neighborhood.

03:47.221 --> 03:48.587
Hey, Detective.

03:50.957 --> 03:52.625
Mr. Scott...

03:52.627 --> 03:54.093
um...

03:54.095 --> 03:56.729
my new partner, Maria Baez.

03:56.731 --> 03:58.197
Joseph.
Good to meet you.

03:58.199 --> 04:00.299
So, you heard,
it's happened again.

04:00.301 --> 04:01.266
Yeah, I heard.

04:01.268 --> 04:02.735
Uh... we caught
the case in fact.

04:02.737 --> 04:05.137
That's great.
It's the same school.

04:05.139 --> 04:06.338
It's the same time of day.

04:06.340 --> 04:08.240
Am I missing something?

04:08.242 --> 04:10.776
Joseph's daughter Allie was
abducted from the same school

04:10.778 --> 04:11.677
seven years ago.

04:11.679 --> 04:14.647
Seven years,
two months, 14 days.

04:14.649 --> 04:17.082
Danny worked 'round the clock
to find Allie.

04:17.084 --> 04:18.617
He puts up with me...

04:18.619 --> 04:21.053
coming by, chewing his ear,
giving him updates.

04:21.055 --> 04:23.622
Yeah, unfortunately, I wasn't
able to bring Allie back to you.

04:23.624 --> 04:25.457
But this is a big break, right?

04:25.459 --> 04:26.959
I mean, whoever took this girl,

04:26.961 --> 04:28.861
maybe they know something
about my Allie.

04:30.564 --> 04:33.832
You know, we kind of
went over this before.

04:33.834 --> 04:35.834
The odds of finding somebody
after all this time...

04:35.836 --> 04:37.269
I know the statistics.

04:37.271 --> 04:39.772
I also know in my heart that
Allie's out there somewhere.

04:39.774 --> 04:41.240
She has to be.

04:42.475 --> 04:44.643
Don't give up on her, Danny.

